description:
PROBLEM: §5.5 (Comparison Blocks, lines 2426-2441) defines the format for side-by-side ❌ SUBOPTIMAL vs ✅ CHOSEN comparisons but the meta-standard never uses this format in its own content. ADR-004 (Self-Bootstrapping) requires DDIS to demonstrate every element it prescribes. Several ADRs in §0.6 contain WHY NOT annotations and options analysis, but none use the explicit comparison block format from §5.5.

FIX: Add one comparison block instance to DDIS's own content. Best location: within an existing ADR or implementation choice. Candidate: the two-tier vs three-tier decision in §0.13.3 or §0.13.7 could include a compact comparison block:

// ❌ SUBOPTIMAL: Two-tier for large specs (>20 invariants)
//   - Constitution: ~1,500 lines (30-37% of budget consumed before module starts)
//   - Module budget: ~3,500 lines maximum (insufficient for complex subsystems)
// ✅ CHOSEN: Three-tier with domain grouping
//   - Constitution: ~350 + ~400 = ~750 lines (15% of budget)
//   - Module budget: ~4,250 lines (sufficient for complex subsystems)
//   - See ADR-006 for full analysis

~8-10 lines added. Alternatively, place in §0.8.2 comparing domain-spec vs meta-standard proportional weights.

INVARIANTS ADDRESSED: ADR-004 (Self-Bootstrapping — demonstrate the element). INV-001 (Causal Traceability — the comparison block traces to ADR-006). INV-007 (earns its place by enriching an existing section with quantified reasoning).
